author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A ferry, KMP Tunu Pratama Jaya, sank in rough seas near Bali, Indonesia, shortly after departing from Ketapang port in East Java. The incident resulted in at least four fatalities, with many individuals still missing. The ferry was carrying 65 people and 22 vehicles. Search and rescue operations are ongoing, involving multiple boats amidst challenging wave conditions.
title: Four dead, 38 missing after ferry sinks in Indonesia - rescuers battle rough sea

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Bangladesh suffered a shocking collapse in the first ODI against Sri Lanka, losing seven wickets for five runs. Chasing 245, they crumbled from 100 for 1 to 167 all out, handing Sri Lanka a 77-run victory. Wanindu Hasaranga's 4 for 10 and Charith Asalanka's century were pivotal for Sri Lanka.
title: From 100/1 to 105/8! B'desh collapse under lights as SL seal stunning win

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Captain Shubman Gill's unbeaten century, coupled with Ravindra Jadeja's support, propelled India to 310/5 on Day 1 at Edgbaston. Former England pacer Steven Finn noted the shortened boundaries, linking it to England's 'Bazball' approach. Gill's captaincy and Jaiswal's aggressive start put India in a strong position despite Woakes' early breakthroughs.
title: IND v ENG: Boundaries brought in for Bazball? Ex-Eng cricketer's claim raises eyebrows

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Rumors are swirling about a potential return of Nazem Kadri to the Toronto Maple Leafs, but insiders like David Pagnotta consider it unlikely. Despite Kadri's impressive performance and the Leafs' need for toughness, his hefty contract and Calgary's desire to stay competitive pose significant obstacles. While a Kadri reunion appeals to fans, it remains a long shot.
title: NHL Trade Rumors: Insider rules out Nazem Kadri’s Maple Leafs return

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi received ‘The Officer of the Order of the Star of Ghana’ from President John Mahama, marking the first visit by an Indian Prime Minister to Ghana in over three decades. Modi dedicated the award to the youth of both nations, their shared history, and cultural diversity.
title: 'Officer of the Order of the Star': PM Modi receives Ghana's top state honour

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The US State Department has emphasized that applicants for student visas must understand the visa's purpose is to study, not to disrupt campuses or obstruct other students. Deputy spokesperson Mignon Houston stressed that visa decisions prioritize national security.
title: US welcomes foreign students to apply for visa but issues stark warning

author: DWAIPAYAN GHOSH
description: Monojit Mishra, the primary suspect in the law student gang-rape case, instructed aides to monitor the police station after the crime. He and another accused contacted college officials and seniors for help, but were refused. Mishra and another accused were arrested near Ballygunge railway station, with police collecting evidence, including a bed cover from the scene.
title: Kolkata horror: 'Mango' was 'confident' assault video would keep survivor mum

author: TNN
description: Following Group Captain Shubhanshu Shukla's arrival at the ISS, ISRO emphasizes international collaboration in space exploration, drawing parallels with Rakesh Sharma's 1984 mission. The Axiom-4 mission, conceptualized during PM Modi's US visit, will provide crucial data for the Gaganyaan program, focusing on astronaut health and mission safety.
title: Axiom-4 one small step in orbit, giant leap for spaceflight & discovery: Isro

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Ravi Shastri lauded Shubman Gill's disciplined century against England, highlighting his improved defence and control. Gill's unbeaten 114, along with a crucial partnership with Ravindra Jadeja, helped India reach 310/5 at stumps on Day 1. Experts emphasise the importance of India capitalising on this foundation to avoid a collapse and aim for a substantial total on Day 2.
title: IND vs ENG: 'Gill looked fantastic, very solid' - Ex-coach hails gritty hundred

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Shubman Gill etched his name in cricket history, becoming only the second Indian captain to score centuries in both the first and second Tests in England. Following his 147 at Headingley, Gill's unbeaten 114 at Edgbaston led India to 310/5, showcasing exceptional leadership under pressure.
title: IND vs ENG: Records galore as Shubman Gill joins Bradman, Sobers in historic feat

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Aamir Khan's 'Sitaare Zameen Par,' released on June 20, 2025, has grossed over Rs 130 crore, demonstrating continued audience interest. The film experienced a significant drop on its thirteenth day, earning approximately Rs 2.75 crore. Despite this dip and upcoming competition from 'Metro In Dino,' Aamir Khan expresses delight at the audience's positive reception to the film's heartwarming story.
title: 'Sitaare Zameen Par' box office: Aamir Khan's film sees major drop; mints over Rs 2cr

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: CoreWeave Inc.'s stock has surged nearly 300% since its March IPO, elevating CEO Michael Intrator into the world's wealthiest. Intrator's net worth reached $10.3 billion, fueled by investor enthusiasm for AI and tech IPOs. The rally has also significantly increased the wealth of co-founders and early investors, marking a hot streak for IPOs in 2025.
title: AI wealth boom: This CEO joins world’s richest; 300% stock surge fuels rise

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Sean "Diddy" Combs was denied bail after being convicted on federal prostitution charges, despite acquittal on sex trafficking and racketeering allegations. Judge Arun Subramanian cited the seriousness of the evidence and a pattern of violence as reasons for keeping Combs in custody. The defense argued against detention, but the prosecution emphasized Combs' wealth, violence, and disregard for the law.
title: Diddy denied bail; convicted of prostitution charges; acquitted of sex trafficking

author: TNN
description: During a meeting between S Jaishankar and Pete Hegseth, the US expressed optimism about finalizing pending defence sales to India and enhancing defence industrial cooperation. Both leaders acknowledged concerns regarding aggression in the Asia-Pacific region. Jaishankar also met with Marco Rubio, affirming the robust US-India relationship and discussing collaboration on trade, defence, and other areas.
title: In meet with Jaishankar, US def secy seeks completion of pending defence sales

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Vishnu Manchu's mythological drama 'Kannappa,' featuring star cameos, is experiencing a dip in box office collections after a strong opening. The film earned an estimated Rs 1.15 crore on Wednesday, bringing its total to approximately Rs 27.5 crore. While the Telugu version maintains decent occupancy, the Hindi version shows a more subdued response.
title: 'Kannappa' box office: Vishnu Manchu's mythological drama sees a dip; earns Rs 27.5cr

author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
description: Outrage has exploded in Pakistan's Balochistan after the killing of activist Zeeshan Ahmed, allegedly by military personnel. Zeeshan, who sought the return of his forcibly disappeared father, was abducted on June 29th and his body was discovered the next day. The Baloch Yakjehti Committee reports Zeeshan's body showed signs of torture, including bullet wounds.
title: Pak: Outcry in Baloch over killing of activist after forced disappearance

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
title: Skydiving plane with 15 aboard crashes in New Jersey; at least 5 hospitalised

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: John Cena praised Dave Bautista's acting skills. Cena called Bautista the greatest wrestler-turned-actor. He highlighted Bautista's range and physical transformations for roles. Bautista gained fame as Drax in the MCU. He has appeared in films like Blade Runner 2049 and Glass Onion. Cena acknowledged Bautista's success in both wrestling and Hollywood. Both Cena and Bautista transitioned from WWE to acting.
title: WWE Champ John Cena names surprise GOAT; wrestling icon turned actor stuns fans
